Native, Data and Voice Vlans
===============================

native VLAN by default is the default Vlan - VLAN 1

when encapsulation from 802.1q is used, we have native Vlan.
802.1q trunk ports adds VLAN Headers on all frames. 
All frames from native vlan or vlan 1 are sent out on 802.1q trunks untagged.
							                                                      ---------

If tagged- frames has source vlan header.
If untagged - frames does not have source vlan header.
                              ---------


Types of Data
1. Voice - traffic from Phone
2. Data - traffic from the PC
	Using VoIP Phone we can connect to Switch and to PCs via ethernet port


